22:
That's right, a whole bunch of them.
And the corpses look like they've
been sucked dry. Even the grass and
flowers around them are withered
for some reason.
26:
Hm... But isn't that forest occupied
by the rangers that work for the
Guild?
30:
Yeah, they're certainly a suspicious
lot... Sure would be nice if we could
do a proper investigation into them,
doncha think?
35:
I see where this is going... Very well,
we'll take on this request.
39:
Thank you! Figuring this out'll raise
my quarterly evaluation for sure!
43:
...You sure you want to say that out
loud?
52:
Those were the eyes of the
hunted—not the hunter. Our target
must be up ahead.
70:
Step away from the girl, unless you
wanna end up like those beasts.
72:
Now you've done it, Primula... How're
you gonna make up for it this time?
78:
We'll decide your punishment later...
Let's go.
81:
Hold it. What are your intentions for
this girl?
84:
As members of the Adventurer's
Guild, it is our duty to report what
happens out in the field... You
rangers also work for the Guild,
correct?
87:
Hmph... This is our problem. We'll
deal with it however we see fit.
90:
That doesn't answer our question.
What are you going to do to her?
93:
Don't know what you're getting so
worked up for. This crybaby can't
even control her powers. She's a
walking disaster waiting to happen.
95:
This ain't no princess you should be
white-knighting for.
101:
I-I'm sorry... I-I promise I'll do better...
So please—
104:
I've heard THAT before. Is this what
you call "doing better"?
106:
We might've had a deal with your
daddy, but taking you in was the
worst mistake of our lives.
107:
All you have to do is stay out of our
way, Primula. You can manage that
much at least, can't you?
111: Ah, I... I wasn't trying to—
115: Do you wish to go with them?
122: O-of course not... I hate it here...
124: But... I have nowhere else to go...
129: Then why don't you come with us?
137: I like the way you think, Stella.
140:
This girl's coming with us. If you don't
like it, take it up with the Guild later.
143:
And don't even think of trying to take
her back now... You're gonna have to
get through me first.
147:
Hmph... You'll regret taking in that
crybaby, kid.
151:
How are you feeling? Are you hurt
anywhere?
161: Heh... How about we talk over dinner?
170:
Worry not, child. No one here intends
you any harm.
173:
You can take your time explaining
the situation as well. Does that
sound good?
182:
So your father could also use the
same magic as you, huh? But why
would he work with those rangers?
187:
Everyone living in the forest is
required to do so. But then... both of
my parents passed away... so I had
to take his place...
190:
However... I don't exactly... have the
best control of my powers...
193:
A-and when I worry about doing a
good job, they get even harder to
control...
197:
...Even a mouse will bite when
backed into a corner. You were
simply defending yourself.
199:
Since returning is out of the
question... Do you have any relatives
outside the forest? Perhaps we can
make use of those connections...
209:
Quit your stammering and spit it
out. You got a place to stay or not?
214:
Don't worry about Nimbus. His growl
is worse than his bite.
219:
You can worry about the future later.
For now, why don't you just focus on
getting your bearings?
230:
I-I'm sorry! Wh-when I get nervous,
my powers—
Ah, d-don't worry, these flowers
won't hurt anyone!
235:
R-right. Sorry, I was just a little
surprised is all... 
As long as they're not dangerous...
240:
Actually, now that I take a look... 
Your magic is really pretty.
251:
Goodness! Where are all these
petals coming from?!
255: We could very well be buried alive.
260: I-I'm sorry... I didn't mean to... Oh...
